  4class WordsizeTreeSet():
  5
  6  def __init__(self, u: int, a: Iterable[int]=[]):
  7    assert u > 0
  8    self.u = u
  9    data = []
 10    len_ = 0
 11    if a:
 12      u >>= 5
 13      A = array('I', bytes(4*(u+1)))
 14      for a_ in a:
 15        assert 0 <= a_ < u, \
 16            f'ValueError: {self.__class__.__name__}.__init__, {a_}, u={u}'
 17        if A[a_>>5] >> (a_&31) & 1 == 0:
 18          len_ += 1
 19          A[a_>>5] |= 1 << (a_&31)
 20      data.append(A)
 21      while u:
 22        a = array('I', bytes(4*((u>>5)+1)))
 23        for i in range(u+1):
 24          if A[i]:
 25            a[i>>5] |= 1 << (i&31)
 26        data.append(a)
 27        A = a
 28        u >>= 5
 29    else:
 30      while u:
 31        u >>= 5
 32        data.append(array('I', bytes(4*(u+1))))
 33    self.data: List[array[int]] = data
 34    self.len: int = len_
 35    self.len_data: int = len(data)

 37  def add(self, x: int) -> bool:
 38    assert 0 <= x < self.u, \
 39        f'ValueError: {self.__class__.__name__}.add({x}), u={self.u}'
 40    if self.data[0][x>>5] >> (x&31) & 1: return False
 41    self.len += 1
 42    for a in self.data:
 43      a[x>>5] |= 1 << (x&31)
 44      x >>= 5
 45    return True

 47  def discard(self, x: int) -> bool:
 48    assert 0 <= x < self.u, \
 49        f'ValueError: {self.__class__.__name__}.discard({x}), u={self.u}'
 50    if self.data[0][x>>5] >> (x&31) & 1 == 0: return False
 51    self.len -= 1
 52    for a in self.data:
 53      a[x>>5] &= ~(1 << (x&31))
 54      x >>= 5
 55      if a[x]: break
 56    return True

 58  def ge(self, x: int) -> Optional[int]:
 59    assert 0 <= x < self.u, \
 60        f'ValueError: {self.__class__.__name__}.ge({x}), u={self.u}'
 61    data = self.data
 62    d = 0
 63    while True:
 64      if d >= self.len_data or x>>5 >= len(data[d]): return None
 65      m = data[d][x>>5] & ((~0) << (x&31))
 66      if m == 0:
 67        d += 1
 68        x = (x >> 5) + 1
 69      else:
 70        x = (x >> 5 << 5) + (m & -m).bit_length() - 1
 71        if d == 0: break
 72        x <<= 5
 73        d -= 1
 74    return x

 76  def gt(self, x: int) -> Optional[int]:
 77    assert 0 <= x < self.u, \
 78        f'ValueError: {self.__class__.__name__}.gt({x}), u={self.u}'
 79    if x + 1 == self.u: return
 80    return self.ge(x + 1)

 82  def le(self, x: int) -> Optional[int]:
 83    assert 0 <= x < self.u, \
 84        f'ValueError: {self.__class__.__name__}.le({x}), u={self.u}'
 85    data = self.data
 86    d = 0
 87    while True:
 88      if x < 0 or d >= self.len_data: return None
 89      m = data[d][x>>5] & ~((~1) << (x&31))
 90      if m == 0:
 91        d += 1
 92        x = (x >> 5) - 1
 93      else:
 94        x = (x >> 5 << 5) + m.bit_length() - 1
 95        if d == 0: break
 96        x <<= 5
 97        x += 31
 98        d -= 1
 99    return x

101  def lt(self, x: int) -> Optional[int]:
102    assert 0 <= x < self.u, \
103        f'ValueError: {self.__class__.__name__}.lt({x}), u={self.u}'
104    if x - 1 == 0: return
105    return self.le(x - 1)

114    v = self.get_min()
